				<h1>OWL | Occupant Wellbeing through Lighting</h1>
				<p>This is the documentation of OWL: an opensource workflow in Rhino Grasshopper developed for performing spectral lighting simulations, and evaluating non-image-forming effects of light on occupant wellbeing. </p>
				<p>This tool uses parsimonious approach with minimal inputs, for evaluating the following NIF metrics: <b>Melanopic metrics</b> (subset of alpha-opic metrics) recommended by CIE as part of CIES026 standard, and <b>Circadian metrics</b> proposed by Lighting Research Centre.</p> 
				<p>This is developed by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marshal-maskarenj">Marshal Maskarenj</a> at <a href="https://uclouvain.be/fr/facultes/loci">LAB/LOCI UCLouvain</a>, along with <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bertrand-deroisy-a3411a5/">Bertrand Deroisy</a> and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sergio-altomonte-81341b4/">Sergio Altomonte</a>; as part of the <a href="https://www.frs-fnrs.be/en/">FNRS</a> funded project SCALE (Shading Control Algorithms for Luminance Evaluation).</p>
				<button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg">Tell Me More!</button>
			</div>			
