					<h3 class="feature-title">Lorem ipsum</h3>
					<img src="images/column-1.jpg" class="img-fluid">
					<p>The LRC toolbox (Circadian Light Combined Calculator) is used to evaluate Circadian Lighting and Circadian Stimulus metrics. For the mathematical models used, <a href="https://www.lrc.rpi.edu/programs/lightHealth/index.asp">this publicly available toolbox</a> can be referred.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-12">
					<h3 class="feature-title">Lorem ipsum</h3>
					<img src="images/column-2.jpg" class="img-fluid">
					<p>The outputs of α-opic irradiance, α-opic Efficacy of Luminous Radiation (ELR), α-opic Daylight Efficacy Ratio (DER), and α-opic Equivalent Daylight Illuminance (EDI) are evaluated using the approach taken in the CIES026 toolbox. These outputs represent the alpha-opic metrics (or melanopic metrics, when alpha-type is set at melanopic) recommended by CIE. For the mathematical models deployed in this component, <a href="https://cie.co.at/publications/cie-system-metrology-optical-radiation-iprgc-influenced-responses-light-0">this publicly available toolbox</a> can be referred.</p>
				</div>
				
